  "learn": {
    "heading": "What is a prime number?",
    "intro": "<p>A <strong>prime</strong> number has exactly two factors: 1 and itself (like 2, 3, 5, 7). A <strong>composite</strong> number can be split into smaller factors. <strong>Prime factorization</strong> means writing a number as a product of only primes.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>12:</strong> split into 2 × 6, then split 6 into 2 × 3. So 12 = <strong>2 × 2 × 3</strong> — all primes.",
      "Check yourself: multiply the primes back. 2 × 2 × 3 = 12. ✔"
    ]
  },
